We have that \begin{align*}
z^2-40z+340\le 4&\implies z^2-40z+336\le 0\\
&\implies (z-12)(z-28)\le 0.
\end{align*}The product of two numbers is less than or equal to zero if one of the numbers is nonpositive and the other is nonnegative.  Thus, we have two cases: \begin{align*}
z-12\ge 0\text{ and }z-28\le 0&\implies z\ge 12\text{ and }z\le 28\\
&\implies \boxed{[12,28]}\end{align*}or \begin{align*}
z-12\le 0\text{ and }z-28\ge 0&\implies z\le 12\text{ and }z\ge 28\\
&\implies \text{no solutions}.
\end{align*}Thus, the only solutions are in the interval $\boxed{[12,28]}$.

