The length of $PR$ is the hypotenuse of a right triangle with legs of length $10\sqrt{2}$.  Therefore, $PR = \sqrt{(10\sqrt{2})^2 + (10\sqrt{2})^2} = \sqrt{200 + 200} = \sqrt{400} = \boxed{20}$.

