answer:
Let the side length of the larger square be $s$.  Then $s^2 = 60$, so $s = \sqrt{60} = 2\sqrt{15}$.

[asy]
pair a=(0,1),b=(1,0),c=(0,-1),d=(-1,0);
draw((-1,-1)--(-1,1)--(1,1)--(1,-1)--cycle);
draw(a--b--c--d--cycle);
