label("$s$",(0,1/2),W);
label("$s$",(1/2,0),N);
label("$s$",(0,-1/2),E);
label("$s$",(1/2,0),S);
label("$x$",(1/2,1/2),NE);
draw((1/2,1/2)--(1/2,-1/2)--(-1/2,-1/2)--(-1/2,1/2)--cycle,linetype("8 8"));
[/asy]

The side length of the smaller square is the diagonal of a square with side length $s/2$.  Therefore, the side length of the smaller square is $(s/2)\sqrt{2} = \frac{s\sqrt{2}}{2} = \frac{2\sqrt{15}\sqrt{2}}{2} = \sqrt{30}$.  The area of the smaller square is $(\sqrt{30})^2 = \boxed{30}$.

