Let $\mathbf{a}, \mathbf{b}, \mathbf{c}, \mathbf{p}$ be the position vectors of points $A, B, C, P,$ respectively.  Then
\[\mathbf{p} - \mathbf{a} + 2 (\mathbf{p} - \mathbf{b}) + 3 (\mathbf{p} - \mathbf{c}) = \mathbf{0},\]so $6 \mathbf{p} = \mathbf{a} + 2 \mathbf{b} + 3 \mathbf{c},$ or $\mathbf{p} = \frac{1}{6} \mathbf{a} + \frac{1}{3} \mathbf{b} + \frac{1}{2} \mathbf{c}.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.6 cm);

pair A, B, C, P;

A = (2,5);
B = (0,0);
C = (6,0);
P = (13/6,5/3);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(A--P);
draw(B--P);
draw(C--P);

