answer:
We have that $f(x)=\frac{x-3}{x-4}$, so $f^{-1}(x)$ is the inverse of $f(x)$. To find the inverse, we switch the $x$ and $y$ and solve for $y$:
\begin{align*}
x&=\frac{y-3}{y-4}\\
x(y-4)&=y-3\\
xy-4x&=y-3\\
xy-y&=4x-3\\
y(x-1)&=4x-3\\
y&=\frac{4x-3}{x-1}
\end{align*}
Thus, $f^{-1}(x)=\frac{4x-3}{x-1}$. The only value that makes this undefined is $x=\boxed{1}$.

